#Text=Fort Wayne
#Text=Fort
#Text=Wayne
#Text=is a city in the northeastern part of Indiana a state of the United States of America .
#Text=It is 30 minutes from the western Ohio border and 70 minutes from the southern border of Michigan .
#Text=With a population of around 260,00 in the city and 615,000 in the metropolitan area , it 's Indiana 's second largest city .
#Text=Fort Wayne is a metropolitan city with a small community feel .
#Text=It provides the rush of urban activity while never losing an intimate personal connection with those who live or visit here .
#Text=Fort Wayne is the second largest city in the state of Indiana , located in Allen County , the largest county in the state by geography .
#Text=It is the regional commerce and industry center for Northeast Indiana and also impacts the economies of Southwestern Michigan and Western Ohio .
#Text=Fort Wayne has been and is a breeding ground for entrepreneurs and high tech industries .
#Text=The city has many historical buildings that usually offer regular tours .
#Text=The city itself has a long history going back to the 1700s , but has lately succumbed to the urban sprawl so widespread in the Midwest .
#Text=It is nicknamed the " Summit City " because , even though the surrounding area seems completely flat , it is on the high point of the old Wabash-Erie canal .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Fort Wayne International Airport ( FWA ) .
#Text=Recommended to passengers looking for the convenient and friendly way to travel .
#Text=Recognized as " the nation 's friendliest airport " by USA Today .
#Text=FWA 's airlines offer daily direct flights to/from Atlanta , Chicago , Cincinnati , Cleveland , Detroit , and Dallas-Fort Worth .
#Text=With free wireless internet throughout the terminal , ample parking , short security lines and access to hundreds of destinations worldwide .
#Text=Fort Wayne International Airport operates 24 hours a day , 7 days a week .
#Text=It 's served by commuter and regional jets from most of the major hubs in the country .
#Text=The airport has free internet ( wireless or in carrels upstairs on the secure side ) .
#Text=There is a cookie factory right across the street from the airport , and you can tell what they 're baking that day by smell .
#Text=Volunteers meet you when you arrive and give away free cookies as you come through security .
#Text=For flights to Chicago , expect to pack your hand luggage into a small cargo hull .
#Text=It is recommended that you avoid packing anything fragile in your carry-ons .
#Text=The smaller lines operate tiny planes in between FW and Chicago and there is little room for even ladies ' purses .
#Text=There is a shuttle bus service between Indianapolis and Fort Wayne run by Hoosier Shuttle .
#Text=By car
#Text=Interstates 69 makes Fort Wayne easily accessible by car from the north and south .
#Text=It connects to Indianapolis , in the south and Lansing , to the north .
#Text=I-469 is an southern and eastern interstate by-pass of Fort Wayne that connects with I-69 at both ends .
#Text=U.S. 24 is an important expressway and connects to Toledo , Ohio in the northeast and Lafayette , Indiana , to the southwest .
#Text=U.S. 27 is an important highway , providing access primarily from places to the south and is the main north-south highway through downtown .
#Text=U.S. 30 is an important expressway , providing access primarily from places to the west and east .
#Text=It connects to Lima , Ohio in the east and Valparaiso , to the west .
#Text=U.S. 33 is an important highway , providing access primarily from places to the northwest and south .
#Text=It connects to Columbus , Ohio in the south and Goshen and Elkhart , to the northwest .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Greyhound has multiple long-haul services to Fort Wayne from most nearby cities .
#Text=The is located downtown at 121 W Baker St.
#Text=By train
#Text=Fort Wayne is not directly served by passenger rail , but Amtrak has several daily services to nearby Waterloo , half an hour north of Fort Wayne .
#Text=Be prepared to phone for a cab or have someone meet you because transportation from the station to the city is limited .
#Text=The station is served by Capitol Limited between Washington D.C. and Chicago as well at the Lare Shore Limited between New York , Boston and Chicago .
#Text=By bus
#Text=There is a municipal bus system that can get you around called Citilink .
#Text=The system has limited routes and hours of operation .
#Text=By car
#Text=To get into downtown US 27 would be the main route from north or south and Jefferson Boulevard from the west .
#Text=From the east the route to downtown Fort Wayne Washington Boulevard and would pass through New Haven .
#Text=All major Rental Car Companies have franchises are at the airport , but do n't rent here .
#Text=The airport branches are much more expensive .
#Text=Call the Enterprise Car Rental location on the SW or NE side and have them pick you up .
#Text=They have a weekend rate for $ 9.95 a day , from Friday morning through Monday morning .
#Text=Reserve other rates online for the best rates .
#Text=If you get into the airport on a late flight , do n't assume there will be taxis waiting .
#Text=Call ahead and arrange one on A-1 taxi at 260-478-9910 or 800-871-0518 .
#Text=Museums and History
#Text=Allen County Public Library Genealogical Collection .
#Text=It is the largest public genealogical collection in the United States .
#Text=The library offers special classes and has librarians there to assist you in your search .
#Text=One night a year , they keep the room open until midnight .
#Text=It is usually around Halloween .
#Text=The Fort Wayne History Center , 302 E Berry St , ☏ +1 260-426-2882 .
#Text=Is a museum with many interesting displays about the area , from the days before Europeans came , to modern times .
#Text=Even the castle-like building is worth a careful look .

#Text=Among the stories to be read there are the afternoon that hi fidelity sound ( from separating the frequencies and routing them through different speakers ) was invented at the local Magnavox plant .
#Text=They had settled on the term " tweeter " for the small speaker , but rejected a number of other suggestions before settling on " woofer " for the big ones .
#Text=Fort Wayne Firefighters Museum ( Engine House No. 3 ) , 226 W Washington Blvd , ☏ +1 260-426-0051 .
